{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-film-lead-project-js","path":"/scroll/","result":{"data":{"prismicFilmLeadProject":{"uid":"scroll","id":"0caaf355-3701-550e-a3b4-bd93cdadcf75","data":{"project_title":{"html":"<p>Scroll</p>","text":"Scroll"},"client":{"html":"<p>Glasgow School of Art</p>","text":"Glasgow School of Art"},"location":{"html":"<p>Glasgow, UK</p>","text":"Glasgow, UK"},"team":{"html":"<p>Theo Ford, Benji Cluness</p>","text":"Theo Ford, Benji Cluness"},"year":{"html":"<p>2016</p>","text":"2016"},"categories":[{"category":{"slug":"performance","id":"ZMfXghAAACEAPtCJ"}},{"category":{"slug":"film","id":"ZMfXYxAAACEAPs_m"}}],"body1":[{"id":"text$727279d8-a4d8-4bac-81ee-208f4cc58968","slice_type":"text","primary":{"text":{"html":"<p>A selection of films exploring the &#39;scroll&#39; interaction. The project sought to explore the concept of scrolling within a wider context than digital media, and provoke questions about our behaviours on the web in relation to our personal lives and interpersonal relationships. In addition to portraying the scroll bar in an animated light, to explore its function in human or relatable terms.</p><p>The process driven research was extensive, including: 3D printing hat clips to create 1st person videos using an iPhone, a pulley system to move objects based on command, and hitting things with sticks.</p>","text":"A selection of films exploring the 'scroll' interaction. The project sought to explore the concept of scrolling within a wider context than digital media, and provoke questions about our behaviours on the web in relation to our personal lives and interpersonal relationships. In addition to portraying the scroll bar in an animated light, to explore its function in human or relatable terms. The process driven research was extensive, including: 3D printing hat clips to create 1st person videos using an iPhone, a pulley system to move objects based on command, and hitting things with sticks."}}},{"id":"video_wi